A MAN suspected of killing a mum and her daughter has abandoned bail. The 32-year-old appeared in the Balfour Magistrates Court, Mpumalanga, on Thursday 9 June and was not asked to plead. The suspect is facing two counts of murder for the deaths of a 24-year-old woman and her two-year-old daughter. Brigadier Selvy Mohlala said the two bodies were discovered on Monday 6 June at their house in Siyathemba squatter camp in Balfour. “Police received information that there had been a murder. “When they got there, they found a woman lying on the kitchen floor. ALSO READ |
Boyfriend kept raping me! “A girl’s body was found in the bedroom with an injury to her neck. “They were both certified dead at the scene,” he said. “It appears that the woman’s other child, a five-month-old boy, was allegedly taken by his father and he’s unharmed.” Police arrested the suspect. It was later revealed the woman was strangled. Provincial commissioner Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela said: “We appreciate the determination and commitment displayed by the police in this investigation. “The police will continue to fight the scourge of crime against women and children.” The matter has been postponed until 11 July.